## Runtime Architecture

- `server.js` is a thin shim that requires `./modules/crm/core/server`.
- `modules/crm/core/server.js` initializes the database, runs migrations, seeds data/lists, loads routes, serves static files, starts reminder checks, and cleans expired sessions.
- `modules/crm/core/app.js` provides the small router and route table.
- `modules/crm/core/routeLoader.js` registers all CRM backend route modules.
- `modules/crm/middleware/auth.js` provides auth, manager checks, ownership filters, manager counts, and null coercion helpers.
- `modules/crm/database/database.js` owns SQLite setup, schema creation, migrations, seed data, and seed list values.

## URL Routing

- `/`: global login page from `main/login.html`
- `/home`: global home page from `main/home.html`
- `/dashboard`: legacy redirect to `/home`
- `/crm`: CRM SPA from `modules/crm/frontend/index.html`
- `/crm/*`: CRM frontend static files
- `/erp/<submodule>`: ERP frontend stubs
- `/api/*`: backend API routes from CRM modules
- Other static paths such as `/css/*`: served from `main/`

