## Development Notes

- No build step is required.
- Prefer `npm run dev` while editing so nodemon restarts automatically.
- Database files are intentionally ignored by nodemon in the dev script.
- API routes use native Node request/response objects augmented with `res.status()` and `res.json()`.
- Non-GET and non-DELETE API requests parse JSON request bodies unless the request is multipart.
- Multipart streams are left unconsumed so route handlers can parse uploads.
- Static serving falls back to `index.html` for SPA-style routes.
- `modules/crm/core/routeLoader.js` is the place to register new backend route modules.

